Step 1) make sure to have the jacc.jar in your PATH (download from http://web.cecs.pdx.edu/~mpj/jacc/)
Step 2) run the parserGenerator.bat (or open a terminal and run jacc arl.jacc in this folder)
Step 3) copy the content of the 2 .java generated files to %at.jku.isse.designspace.rule.arl.parser%
Obs: do not replace the content of ArlParser.java that is written below the // ------------------- hand-written code --------------------- comment

Step 4) change the arl.flex file to include new tokens
Step 5) generate the ARLScanner class from the arl.flex using Jflex (https://www.jflex.de/)
Step 6) copy the ARLScanner file to the parser directory
OBS: depending on the version of Jflex used, some errors will appear (most casting). One error is related to the constructor of ARLScanner. In this case,
create a new constructor using the code below:

/**
   * Creates a new scanner
   *
   * @param   in  the java.io.Reader to read input from.
   */
  public ArlScanner(java.io.InputStream in) {
    this(new java.io.InputStreamReader(in));
  } 